<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &gt; Now if we are planning on conquering space anyway, and colonising every place that can be made habitable, humanity will take centuries to fill up those places. Simply because there is an almost endless amount of space out there. Maybe thousands of years before any sign of congestion appears. Maybe never. Even if 10 children families become the norm. That doesn't mean farming will be kept down to the levels required to feed current population levels. To be on the safe side everyone will ofcourse try and grow extra. What do you do with it if you can't eat it? You sell it. The amount of space available for off Earth agriculture is staggering.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
