I've considered all that. OTEC doesn't seem all that useful. Neither it nor all the other options compete to the tune of a few tens of GW, for the comparable investment on the ground of some hectares of wire mesh and rectiifier diodes.<br>
 They're making inroads towards settling some of the questions regarding useful OTECs, but it still doesn't look as good as Savage made it out, or even too useful in a marginal fashion. Too small scale, and too difficult to scale it up to true industrial levels.<br>
 The LUF is keeping informed with all the current status of OTEC, and they seem to still have their thoughts on hold about using it as any kind of serious leverage on the future.<br>
<br>
If a laser thermal launch site were located nearby the concrete floating city, along with a spaceport using floating barge platforms (lots of LOX/LH2), and if tanker ports were handy for cargos of LPG, then 10GW isn't too much overkill.<br>
<br>
And space efforts have far far more eventual payoff, as well as seemingly as few, or less serious technical problems preventing it from being viable.<br>
